data: {"type":"response.reasoning_summary_text.done","item_id":"rs_0cd27d1b0d94de9e016a04a3048eb88197b410e5231a2079e4","output_index":0,"sequence_number":103,"summary_index":0,"text":"**Calculating meeting time and distance**\n\nI need to find out when and where two trains meet, with Paris and Lyon being 470 km apart. The first train leaves Paris at 3 PM, traveling at 80 km/h, and the second leaves Lyon at 4 PM at 100 km/h. \n\nI’m considering the variable t for hours after 3 PM. For t<1, the second train hasn’t started yet, so I focus on t>=1. I’ll set up the equation with the distances they cover to determine when they meet."}

