data: {"type":"response.reasoning_summary_text.done","item_id":"rs_0cd27d1b0d94de9e016a04a3048eb88197b410e5231a2079e4","output_index":0,"sequence_number":220,"summary_index":1,"text":"**Solving for meeting time and distance**\n\nI’ve figured out the equation: 80t + 100t - 100 = 470, which leads to 180t = 570, giving me t = 3.166666... hours or 3 hours and 10 minutes after 3 PM. That means the trains meet at 6:10 PM.  \n\nTo find the distance from Paris, I calculate 80 * t, which equals about 253.33 km. I’m also considering using the relative speed approach after 4 PM and confirm that the meeting time remains the same at 6:10 PM, with the first train covering 253.33 km."}

